"{\"uid\": \"walb.com-2024-08-19-moultrie-welcome-home-carson-tyler-olympics\", \"text\": \"Moultrie, Ga. (WALB) - The city of Moultrie is gearing up to welcome home Moultrie native Carson Tyler with a parade.  Tyler is returning home today from Paris after competing in diving at the 2024 Summer Olympic Games.  The city of Moltrie posted on its Facebook page that a parade will be taking place tonight at 6 p.m.  They are asking residents to wear red, white, and blue to support Tyler.  The parade route is set to start at 1st Street SE in Moultrie, and head towards East Central Avenue where it will take a left, and end on South Main Street near Kirbo Law.  After the parade wraps up, Tyler will go on a stage and the city will read a proclamation in his honor. He will then be presented a key to the city.  Once that wraps up, Tyler will be available to take pictures and sign autographs.  Tyler placed 4th in theMen's 3-meter Diving event, and he also competed in the Men's 10-meter diving event.  Have a news tip or see an error that needs correction?Let us know.Please include the article's headline in your message.  To stay up to date on all the latest news as it develops, follow WALB onFacebookandX (Twitter). For more South Georgia news, download the WALB News app from theApple StoreorGoogle Play.  Copyright 2024 WALB. All rights reserved.\"}"